    </section>

    <p>2</p>
    <p>• The fa­mously wind­ing road runs down­hill from Na­tional Univer­sity of Sin­ga­pore to West Coast High­way.</p>
    <p>• The num­ber of turns is wildly ex­ag­ger­ated. There are 11, not 99, turns.</p>
    <p>• The road is known as an ac­ci­dent hot spot and the 40kmh speed limit is lower than that on most roads in Sin­ga­pore. 3</p>
    <p>• The Tuas Mega Port will be the world’s largest fully au­to­mated ter­mi­nal when com­pleted in 2040.</p>
    <p>• The route to the con­struc­tion site takes drivers through the Jurong in­dus­trial es­tate that has pow­ered Sin­ga­pore’s eco­nomic growth since in­de­pen­dence. 4 40 lamp posts</p>
    <p>• The 2.5km road is a “spare run­way ”. Since 1986, the RSAF has turned it into a tem­po­rary air­craft run­way seven times for fighter jets to take off and land.</p>
    <p>• The long and wide road is favoured by street rac­ers for il­le­gal car and mo­tor­bike rac­ing.</p>


